<font color="#FF0000">VICTIMS OF AGENT ORANGE</font><br>
<tt>Wed Nov 27 22:36:00 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
My Brother, Ralph William Hoffman III, died from complications due to toxic chemical poisoning in July 1987. He was a Seabee who did two tours in Vietnam from 1967-to-1970. He was ill for nearly twenty years and died most horribly in a University of Pittsburgh medical research hospital. I believe that he was yet another victim of Agent Orange contamination. He left no children and lived his short life as if it had no meaning until he realized that death had meaning. My Brother was a remarkable, bright human being who died so that some few people could make money on the misery that was and is Vietnam. You will not see his name on the Wall yet it should be there. He died as senselessly as anyone and everyone who was connected to the madness and horror. If any of his friends read this, please contact me. I would like to have any copies of pictures and to collect your stories about that time. In gratitude. 
